In E5, we need to depend on logical OR operators to handle default values of function
parameters. Whereas in ES6, Default function parameters feature allows parameters to be
initialized with default values if no value or undefined is passed. Let's compare the behavior with
an examples,
let name = 'John'; 
function myFunc() { 
