answer_en:
Sometimes you would like to have a destructured variable with a different name than the
property name. In that case, you'll use a : newName to specify a name for the variable. This
process is called destructuring aliases.
const obj = { x: 1 }; 
// Grabs obj.x as as { otherName } 
const { x: otherName } = obj;

